article.headline: Michigan 75, NC Asheville 54
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) -- Chris Hunter scored 20 points and freshman Ron Coleman added a career-high 17 to lead four Michigan players in double figures as the Wolverines beat North Carolina-Asheville 75-54 Friday afternoon. Courtney Sims and Dion Harris had 11 and 10 points, respectively, for the Wolverines (8-5), who open the Big Ten season Wednesday at Iowa. Brian McCullough scored 14 points and K.J. Garland had 11 for the Bulldogs (3-8), who finished their nonconference schedule with an 0-7 record on the road. Michigan broke the game open with a 15-0 run late in the first half. Hunter highlighted the spurt with two three-point plays, a 3-point basket and a layup. North Carolina-Asheville pulled within 11 points early in the second half, but the Wolverines answered with a 14-1 run to go ahead 65-39 with 7:41 to go in the game. The closest the Bulldogs could get was 67-51 with 3:53 remaining. The Bulldogs kept the game close in the first half, hitting eight of their first 10 field goal attempts. But they missed their next six shots and committed two of their 11 first-half turnovers on eight straight possessions, allowing Michigan to build a double-digit lead.
